Patrick E. Purdy, alias Edward West, was described by as aunt as a loner and a child  alcoholic.
Several months ago he purchased an AK-47 and then returned to his home  town of Stockton where he killed five children and wounded 39 other children as well as  a children at Cleveland Elementary School before taking his own life.
Purdy had an  extensive criminal history, mostly in the Los Angeles area.
Purdy, who had held a variety  of jobs, had lived in Sandy for a time before moving to Lodi, where he listed his mailing  address as that of his grandmother's, although he did not live with her. 
